cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with texture classification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel CNN architecture, which involves integrating a spectral analysis into CNNs. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves image processing, which may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimizing the model with fewer parameters, which may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
